    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Static Typing Example</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            margin: 20px;\n            padding: 20px;\n            border: 2px solid #ccc;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n        }\n        .code {\n            background-color: #f4f4f4;\n            padding: 10px;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;\n            white-space: pre;\n            overflow: auto;\n        }\n        .result {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n            padding: 10px;\n            background-color: #e7f3fe;\n            border: 1px solid #d9edf7;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Static Typing in JavaScript</h1>\n<p>In JavaScript, we typically have dynamic typing, which means variable types can change. However, we can mimic static typing by using TypeScript or by following certain practices in JavaScript.</p>\n\n<h2>Example of Static Typing (Conceptual)</h2>\n<div class=\"code\">\n    type User = {<br>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;id: number;<br>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;name: string;<br>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;age: number;<br>\n    };<br><br>\n\n    function greetUser(user: User): string {<br>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;return `Hello, ${user.name}, you are ${user.age} years old.`;<br>\n    }<br><br>\n\n    const user: User = {<br>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;id: 1,<br>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;name: 'John',<br>\n        &nbsp;&nbsp;age: 30<br>\n    };<br><br>\n\n    console.log(greetUser(user));<br>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Demonstration</h2>\n<button onclick=\"demonstrateStaticTyping()\">Run Static Typing Example</button>\n<div class=\"result\" id=\"result\"></div>\n\n<script>\n    function demonstrateStaticTyping() {\n        // Simulating static typing via comments, since JavaScript is dynamically typed\n        const user = {\n            id: 1,\n            name: 'John',\n            age: 30\n        };\n\n        const result = greetUser(user);\n        document.getElementById('result').innerText = result;\n    }\n\n    function greetUser(user) {\n        // A pretend static check\n        if (typeof user.name !== 'string' || typeof user.age !== 'number') {\n            throw new Error('Incorrect user type');\n        }\n        return `Hello, ${user.name}, you are ${user.age} years old.`;\n    }\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
